                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>1999-06-29</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>A very good approach to IR from a computer science perspective. Well organized and easy to read although some chapter could be dry for a novice. Excellent cover of visualization techniques, digital libraries, and web searching from a conceptual point of view. The reference list is large enough (and up-to-date) to keep you busy reading more material for several weeks.</span>
                  
              
